## Docs 10 Testing 05 Testing Actions Testing if an action has been halted
Docs 10 Testing 05 Testing Actions | filament/filament@5.x | Source: https://github.com/filamentphp/filament/blob/5.x/docs/10-testing/05-testing-actions.md

## Testing if an action has been halted

To check if an action has been halted, you can use `assertActionHalted()`:

```php
use function Pest\Livewire\livewire;

it('stops sending if invoice has no email address', function () {
    $invoice = Invoice::factory(['email' => null])->create();

    livewire(EditInvoice::class, [
        'invoice' => $invoice,
    ])
        ->callAction('send')
        ->assertActionHalted('send');
});
```

